news_header: The National Mediator's office reports progress in mediation regarding a trade dispute, but no agreement has been reached. A trade strike in logistics began on Monday and will extend to grocery stores starting Wednesday.
news_original_title: Kaupan alan työriitaan ei sopua, ruokakauppojen lakko alkaa keskiviikkona
news_text: Approximately 70,000 employees are affected, with around 3,000 locations on strike. The parties involved will reconvene on Friday. The Trade Union assures that food supplies will not run out, although some products may be missing. Wage increases and worker protections remain key issues in negotiations.
